=== ANCESTORS_VOICE ===
# id: 71
# title: The Ancestors' Voice
# chinese_title: 祖先之声
# category: Lore
# mode: dungeon

An ancient audio log plays on a loop in the meditation chamber. The voice speaks in classical Chinese, describing how the first explorers named the stars using radicals — each star name encoding its properties in its characters.

* [Listen and learn the naming system]
  ~ gain_radical("星")
  "名" (míng) — name, to name. Related to learning star names.
* [Translate the classical Chinese narration]
  ~ gain_xp(25)
  "译" (yì) — to translate
* [Search for the speaker's identity]
  ~ gain_xp(15)
  "祖" (zǔ) — ancestor, grandfather
